# Ignore everything by default — this is a public repo and ~/.claude contains
# volatile runtime data and potentially sensitive config (history, session state,
# MCP server settings, etc).
*
.*

# Explicitly track these safe files:
!.gitignore
!CLAUDE.md
!pr-review-loop.md
!python-testing.md

# Claude Code settings (non-sensitive configuration only)
!settings.json

# Agent persona definitions
!agents/
!agents/**

# Custom slash command skills
!skills/
!skills/**

# Architecture Decision Records
!docs/
!docs/**

# Agent persistent memory
!agent-memory/
!agent-memory/**
# Exclude frequently-changing reptile list from version control
agent-memory/lucos-code-reviewer/reptiles.md

# Dispatcher auto-memory (project-scoped persistent memory).
# Track only the memory/ subdirectory — NOT session history, tool results, or
# subagent logs, which live alongside it and must not go into a public repo.
!projects/
!projects/*/
!projects/*/CLAUDE.md
!projects/*/memory/
!projects/*/memory/**

# Infrastructure scripts
!scripts/
!scripts/**
# ...but not log files generated at runtime
scripts/*.log

# GitHub Actions workflows and other repo config
!.github/
!.github/**

# Team config — track config.canonical.json (stripped of runtime state) not config.json
# (config.json is overwritten by Claude Code each session with timestamps, session IDs, etc.)
!teams/
!teams/*/
!teams/*/config.canonical.json

# Infrastructure and convention reference files
!references/
!references/**
